m the\ndiscovery of a new planet and to compute the orbital solution for the binary.\nThe planet is IC 4651 9122b, with a minimum mass of msini = 6.3 MJ and a\nsemi-major axis a = 2.0 AU. The binary companion is NGC 5822 201B, with a very\nlow minimum mass of msini = 0.11 Msun and a semi-major axis a = 6.5 AU, which\nis comparable to the Jupiter distance to the Sun.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Jul 2018 14:37:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-12"}
